						<summary>

						<p>On two pieces of stone lying near an old village site to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 105[3], Sādhāraṇa, Phālguṇa ba. 1, Saturday, corresponding to 1131 A.D., February 15.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the construction of a temple by Āki Reḍḍi, son of [Appi]reḍḍi and Jakkāsāni, and its maintenance by his sons.</p>						

						</summary>
